Description:
Prime River End Location
AUCTION: Saturday, 3rd November at 11am
This cream brick veneer home is ideally positioned on a generous 854 square metre block and only a hope, skip and a jump to the Murray River (approx. 150 metres).
Features renovated kitchen with wall oven, lounge with feature fire surround, sun room and three generous bedrooms. Polished Murray Pine floors, ducted gas heating and ducted evaporative cooling. Covered rear patio, brick 4m x 8m lockup garage with automatic door, and a well fenced yard with easy vehicle access.
Represents a great opportunity for the first home buyer to purchase in a highly sought after location. Arrange your inspection today.

Description:
Well presented three bedroom home
Located in close proximity to Cobram Anglican College, this well presented three bedroom home offers open plan living to lounge/meals/kitchen. The refurbished kitchen offers electric stove and a good amount of storage/benchspace. All three bedrooms are good sizes with all offering built in robes and ceiling fans. The master bedroom also has reverse cycle split system with the second one located to the meals area. The family bathroom has bath, shower and vanity with a separate toilet off the laundry. Across the back of the home is an outdoor entertaining area overlooking a generous size block with garden shed. There is also a single garage with access all the way through into the back yard. This home is excellent value for money and has previously been rented at $280 per week. Book an inspection today.

Description:
Spacious Three Bedroom Family Home
Beautifully renovated three bedroom home in the perfect location. The blackwood timber kitchen features plenty of storage space and quality appliances with an electric wall oven, gas cook top and two drawer dishwasher. The large island bench over looks the open plan dining and lounge making it a great area to entertain! The home boasts a very large rumpus room to the rear of the home, which is a perfect area for the kids. All bedrooms have built in robes with a HUGE ensuite that encompasses shower, bath and toilet off the master bedroom. The home features ducted gas heating, reverse cycle split system and ceiling fans for your all year round comfort. Sited on a great block size of approximately 890sqm with double tandem carport, verandah area, pergola, shedding and lovely established lawns and gardens. What are your waiting for book and inspection today!

Description:
Rustic Charm With A Modern Touch
Sit by the open fireplace with stone mantle and enjoy everything this large four bedroom, two bathroom home has to offer. A rare treat this close to the river with a rustic, yet modern feel.
Gorgeous kitchen with a 3 metre breakfast bar and large stainless steel gas stove and electric oven. Large open plan living and meals area with exposed ceiling beams and timber floating floors. Separate formal lounge with a magnificent fireplace and French doors. Spacious parents retreat at one end of the house with ensuite and walk in robe, and three additional bedrooms including one with a second walk in robe. Doors open from the living area out onto to the fabulous deck and the big rear yard with space galore, a paved entertaining area and garden shed.
All this on a generous 843 square metre block only 5 minutes walk to the Murray River. Only the second time offered for sale in approximately 40 years, don't miss your chance, call today!
